In marketing, a product is an object or system
 made available for consumer use; it is anything
 that can be offered to a market to satisfy the 
desire or need of a customer.[1] In retailing, 
products are often referred to as merchandise,
 and in manufacturing, products are bought as
 raw materials and then sold as finished goods.
 A service is also regarded to as a type of product.
